WIFE of late Singer, Nomoreloss, Adeola Osinuga, is dead. Osinuga, according to family sources, died after a protracted illness, four years after the passing of her late husband. Friends and colleagues said she had been battling the ailment termed, “Fibromyalgia” for about four years, adding that this had kept the On Air Personality with Rhythm FM away from work for a long time. Fibromyalgia, according to experts, is a disorder characterised by widespread musculoskeletal pain, accompanied by fatigue, sleep, memory and mood issues. The late Adeola’s husband, Nomoreloss had died from Pneumonia in March 2016. The late couple got married in 2008 and have a nine-year-old daughter, Mo. 